title: Palo Alto: Threat Database Version
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/network/palo_alto
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check reports the installed Threat (Threat ID) database version of a
 Palo Alto firewall, read from the PAN-COMMON-MIB
 (panSysThreatVersion .1.3.6.1.4.1.25461.2.1.2.1.9).

 The check remembers when the version last changed and applies upper levels
 to the age since that last update. This detects firewalls whose Threat
 database is no longer being updated. Levels can be configured via the rule
 "Palo Alto Threat database age" and default to WARN at one day and CRIT at
 29 hours.

discovery:
 One service is created if the firewall exposes the Threat database version.
